      "content": "```\n# CloudScale User Profile Endpoint\n\n## Overview\nThe `GET /user` endpoint retrieves the profile information for the currently logged-in user. It includes details such as the user's ID, email, and status.\n\n## Endpoint\n`GET /user`\n\n## Response\nReturns a JSON object containing the user's profile information, including:\n- `id`: The unique identifier for the user.\n- `email`: The user's email address.\n- `status`: The user's account status.\n\n## Example Request\n```\nGET /user\n```\n\n## Example Response\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"12345\",\n  \"email\": \"user@example.com\",\n  \"status\": \"active\"\n}\n```\n\n## Usage\nThis endpoint is useful for applications that need to display or process user profile information. It can be used in various scenarios, such as user dashboards, profile management systems, and more.\n\n## Best Practices\n- Ensure that the user is authenticated before making a request to this endpoint.\n- Handle the response appropriately, especially in cases where the user is not found or the status is inactive.\n- Consider implementing caching mechanisms to improve performance for frequent requests.\n\n## Error Handling\n- `404 Not Found`: The user does not exist.",
